help: A zip file of the dlc-models folder from the DLC project which contains the model trained by DLC. The zip file will also contain some summary evaluation_results from the DLC project.

analysis_table_result_column_name: Evaluation Results Error Distribution with p-cutoff Preview
help: Error distributions of the optimal snapshot with p-cutoff. The error type is RMSE in pixels units.

analysis_table_result_column_name: Evaluation Results Score Maps Movie Preview
help: Score maps of training images. Score maps encode the probability that a keypoint occurs at a particular pixel. Each training image is overlaid with a mask of probabilities using a blue-yellow (cold-warm) color scheme. Score maps are computed for the optimal snapshot of the model.

analysis_table_result_column_name: Evaluation Results Test Plots Movie Preview
help: Evaluation results of the optimal snapshot, plotted on test images, with label predictions made by the model and manually set labels. Manually set labels are displayed as a plus symbol '+' and the model's predictions either as a dot (for predictions with a high likelihood) or as an 'x' (for predictions with a low likelihood).

analysis_table_result_column_name: Evaluation Results Locref Maps Movie Preview
help: Locref maps of training images. Locref stands for location refinement layer, which is used to predict offsets to mitigate quantization errors due to downsampled score maps. Location refinement tries to find the position of bodyparts based on their relation to other bodyparts.
Training loss over time, categorized by learning rate.
A zip file containing evaluation results of the trained model including plots of model predictions on labeled data, scoremaps, and locref maps.
Test and training errors of all snapshots evaluated. The optimal snapshot is highlighted in pink on the optimal snapshot metric line.

analysis_table_result_column_name: Evaluation Results Train Plots Movie Preview
help: Evaluation results of the optimal snapshot, plotted on training images, with label predictions made by the model and manually set labels. Manually set labels are displayed as a plus symbol '+' and the model's predictions either as a dot (for predictions with a high likelihood) or as an 'x' (for predictions with a low likelihood).
Error distributions of the optimal snapshot. The error type is RMSE in pixels units.
